race.comment: BAYCAT (1) switched from a Victorian yard and ran the Canberra Maidens off their feet first-up. She will be further improved and draws an inside gate today. Promising and stripping fitter she can take the next step. A BAR IN PARIS (4) also runs along and will have taken benefit from her first-up run in better class. She's come off an Open 2 win at Mudgee and the Baker yard flies at this venue. SHEZASIREN (5) was outgraded at Hawkesbury but was a good Maiden winner here prior when heavily supported. Jumps from the paint today and can't be ruled out. BRUTAL ELEGANCE (3) is in good hands and assess his chances on the nose defeat at Tamworth two back. peaks for this.
